# Upstream boundary — `elastic/observability-migration-platform`

**[elastic/observability-migration-platform](https://github.com/elastic/observability-migration-platform)** is the canonical repository for **`obs-migrate`**, **`grafana-migrate`**, **`datadog-migrate`**, PromQL/Datadog translation, and the shared Kibana YAML/compile path (formerly **elastic/mig-to-kbn**).

## Do not edit `mig-to-kbn/` for workshop-only changes

- **Do not** change files under **`mig-to-kbn/`** to adjust lab behavior, sample dashboards, Instruqt wiring, or one-off demos.
- Put workshop logic and assets in **`assets/`**, **`scripts/`**, **`track_scripts/`**, lab **`assignment.md`**, **`track.yml`**, legacy **`tools/`**, **`agent-skills/`** workshop wrappers, etc.

## Engine work belongs upstream

- Fixes and features for migration CLIs or translators → **[Issues](https://github.com/elastic/observability-migration-platform/issues)** / **[PRs](https://github.com/elastic/observability-migration-platform/pulls)** upstream, then bump this repo with **`./scripts/update_mig_to_kbn.sh`** and commit the vendored tree (optional — Instruqt clones public upstream at bootstrap).

## Vendored tree

- **`mig-to-kbn/`** in this repo is an optional **snapshot** from upstream (default branch **`main`** via **`scripts/update_mig_to_kbn.sh`**). Commits here should be **bumps**, not long-lived forks of the engine. Instruqt **`setup-es3-api`** clones **`observability-migration-platform`** when the vendored tree is absent.
